to generate a data sampling interrupt at the rate of 128 samples per second.  
The microprocessor responds to the data sampling interrupt by setting         
appropriate system flags that are used later in processing the data. The data 
sampling interrupt itself initiates the 'start A/D conversion' in hardware, to
avoid the possibility of small but variable delays in initiating it through   
the software interrupt process.                                               
